// PROTECTED: requires human-in-the-loop approval to edit.
// See tools/hitl/.protected and AGENTS.md (Protected files).

# tools/hitl/.protected
# The canonical list of files that require human-in-the-loop approval
# before any modification. These are the reusable parts of the project's
# HITL (human-in-the-loop) infrastructure — they live in tools/hitl/
# (and the project-level files that govern agent behaviour) and are
# designed to be copy-pasted into other projects as-is.
#
# Policy:
#   1. An agent MUST ask the user before editing any path listed here.
#   2. The user can grant a one-off permission by running
#      `make -f tools/hitl/Makefile protected-allow P=<path>`
#      (writes to tools/hitl/.protected-allowances, which is gitignored).
#   3. The pre-commit hook (tools/hitl/hooks/pre-commit, installable via
#      `make -f tools/hitl/Makefile install-hooks`) refuses any commit
#      that touches a protected file unless the commit message contains
#      the literal string `protected-edit-approved`.
#   4. The agent's primary enforcement is AGENTS.md (the policy section);
#      the hook is the backstop.
#
# Format: one path per line, # for comments, blank lines ignored.
# Paths are repo-relative. Trailing slash for directories. Glob patterns
# (fnmatch) supported.

# --- T1: core HITL infrastructure (highest protection) ---
tools/hitl/Makefile
tools/hitl/check-edit.sh
tools/hitl/.protected

# --- T2: reusable templates and docs ---
tools/hitl/OPENCODE-PERMISSIONS.md

# --- T3: top-level project files governing agent behaviour ---
AGENTS.md
.gitignore
opencode.json
